article.headline: Yale 71, American 59
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Casey Hughes scored 15 points, including 13 in the second half, and Yale defeated American 71-59 Monday night. Dominick Martin scored 14 points and Eric Flato added 13 points and seven assists for the Bulldogs (8-7), who will enter Ivy League play Saturday over .500 for the first time since 2002. Arvydas Eitutavicius led the Eagles (4-10) with a career-high 25 points off the bench in his team's second straight loss. After American pulled within seven at 66-59, but the Bulldogs held the Eagles scoreless for the last 1:58 to preserve the win. Yale took command with a 27-6 run spanning the first and second halves, a spurt that began with seven straight points from Travis Pinick. American cut the lead to 10 three times before Eitutavicius hit a 3-pointer and a slashing layup to make it 63-56 with 2:38 to play. Flato responded with a three-point play off a baseline drive before American's Andre Ingram hit his only field goal, a 3-pointer from the right to bring the Eagles back within seven. The Bulldogs shot 54 percent from 3-point range to the Eagles' 27 percent. ^
